Secured and Monitored Web Infrastructure Design
Overview
This document details a three-server web infrastructure for www.foobar.com with enhanced security features and comprehensive monitoring.
Security Components

1. Firewalls

Purpose:

Control incoming/outgoing traffic
Prevent unauthorized access
Filter malicious traffic
Establish security zones


Placement:

Firewall 1: External traffic protection
Firewall 2: Load balancer protection
Firewall 3: Application server protection
Firewall 4: Database protection



2. SSL/HTTPS Implementation

Purpose:

Encrypt data in transit
Prevent man-in-the-middle attacks
Ensure data integrity
Build user trust


Configuration:

SSL certificate for www.foobar.com
TLS 1.3 protocol
Regular certificate renewal
Strong cipher suites



Monitoring System
1. Monitoring Clients

Purpose:

Collect performance metrics
Track resource utilization
Monitor system health
Alert on issues


Data Collection Methods:

System metrics (CPU, memory, disk)
Application logs
Network statistics
Custom metrics



2. QPS Monitoring

Implementation:
nginx